# UDO Takeover Changelog

## v1.1.0 (2025-01-09)

### Expanded Phase 5 Transition
- **Explicit step-by-step instructions** for AI to follow during transition
- **User confirmation gate** before making any changes
- **Pre-takeover checkpoint** created FIRST before any modifications
- **Detailed file creation instructions** for all UDO core files
- **Clear handoff message** telling user to switch from TAKEOVER_ORCHESTRATOR.md to ORCHESTRATOR.md
- **Transition checklist** to verify all steps completed
- **Rollback instructions** prominently displayed

### Clearer Handoff
- AI now explicitly told to stop reading TAKEOVER_ORCHESTRATOR.md after transition
- User given exact command to continue: "Read ORCHESTRATOR.md and resume this project"
- Safety rollback command highlighted: "Rollback to checkpoint pre-takeover"

## v1.0.0 (2025-01-08)

### Initial Release

#### Takeover Phases
- **Discovery**: Automated project scanning (structure, tech stack, docs, dependencies)
- **Executive Summary**: AI presents understanding for user verification
- **Audit**: Specialist agents assess code quality, security, tests, etc.
- **Synthesis**: Compiled report with options (Quick Wins / Stabilize / Modernize / Rebuild)
- **Transition**: Full UDO installation with findings as todos

#### Audit Agents
- structure-auditor: Architecture and organization
- documentation-auditor: Docs quality and gaps
- code-quality-auditor: Standards, smells, complexity
- security-auditor: Vulnerabilities (with redaction)
- test-auditor: Coverage and quality
- performance-auditor: Bottlenecks
- dependency-auditor: Package health
- ux-auditor: Usability and accessibility
- data-auditor: Schema and integrity

#### Safety Features
- Read-only audit (no changes until user decides)
- Pre-takeover checkpoint
- User verification gates
- Sensitive data redaction
- Explicit uncertainty documentation

#### Integration
- Seamless transition to full UDO system
- Findings converted to prioritized todos
- Audit agents retained as specialists
- Complete audit trail preserved
